[The disease toxoplasmosis can be transmitted by ingestion of either
oocysts (in the feces of cats) or bradyzoites (in raw or undercooked meat,
of just about any animal). Although infections can occur through water,
this is not considered a common method of infection. However, infections in
people can be treated with the combination of pyrimethamine and
sulfonamides. - Mod.TG]
